> Ground chipotle chili is a wonder ingredient: just a dash is enough to bring a smoky and slightly spicy Mexican-style accent to anything it touches. That includes this steak, which deserves a chipot-yay for how it unleashes a wave of flavor via its chipotle lime marinade. The bell pepper and potato hash beneath is no slouch either, supporting with crisp textures and juicy flavors.

== Potato Prep ==

Wash and dry all produce. Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into cubes between ¼ and ½ inch. Place in a medium, #microwave-safe bowl{} with ¼ cup water. Season with @salt{}. Cover bowl with #plastic wrap{}; poke a few holes in wrap with a #fork{} or #small knife{}. Microwave on high for ~{5%minutes}. Drain well and set aside.

Quarter @Lime{1}. Pat @Ranch Steak{10%ounce} dry with a #paper towel{}. Using a fork or sharp #knife{}, poke steak all over. Season with salt and @Chipotle Powder{¼%teaspoon} (we sent more; use up to ½ tsp if you like it spicy). Place on a #plate{} or in a #bowl{}. Squeeze over juice from 1 lime quarter. Set aside to marinate for about ~{5%minutes}.

> We sent more chipotle powder; use up to ½ tsp if you like it spicy.

== Hash ==

Peel and halve @Red Onion{1}, then cut into pieces between ¼ and ½ inch. Core, halve, and seed @Bell Pepper{1}, then cut into pieces between ¼ and ½ inch. Halve @Orange Grape Tomatoes{4%ounce} lengthwise. Trim and slice @Scallions{2}. Heat a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat (use a #nonstick pan{} if you have one).

Add potatoes, 2 tsp @Southwest Spice Blend{1%tablespoon} (save the rest for later), salt, and @pepper{} to pan and toss to evenly coat. Cook without stirring until potatoes are crisp on bottom, ~{3-4%minutes}. Toss and continue to cook until crisp all over, about ~{3%minutes} more. Toss in onion and bell pepper and cook until tender and potatoes are done, about ~{3%minutes}. Toss in tomatoes and half of the scallions. Season with salt and pepper. Set aside while you cook steak.

== Steak ==

Heat a #grill pan{} over medium-high heat.

> TIP: Alternatively, heat a large pan over medium-high heat or a grill with oiled grates over direct heat.

Add steak and cook until charred on bottom, about ~{5%minutes}. Flip and cook to desired doneness, at least ~{3%minutes} more. Set aside off heat to rest for about ~{5%minutes}. Stir together remaining Southwest spice, juice from 1 lime quarter, and @Sour Cream{4%tablespoon} in a #small bowl{}, adding a small splash of water if very thick.

== To Serve ==

Divide hash between #bowls{} or #plates{}. Slice steak against the grain, season with salt, and arrange on top of hash. Drizzle with sour cream mixture. Sprinkle with remaining scallions. Serve with remaining lime quarters.